Uptime Script
======================
*/5 * * * * uptime >> /home/uptime.log
*/5 * * * * ps -eo pcpu,pmem,pid,user,args | sort -k 1 -r | head -10 >> /home/uptime.log
*/5 * * * * date >> /home/uptime.log

   cd /home/
  touch uptime.log
   crontab -e
   /etc/init.d/crond restart
   tail -f uptime.log 
=====================
 
 
 
